      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show reminder URLs in Reminders notes",
        "body": "Closes #59.\n\nKeeps writing the EventKit URL property and mirrors a tool-owned `remindctl URL (managed): ...` line into notes so the link is visible in Reminders.app without treating authored `URL: ...` or plain `remindctl URL: ...` notes as generated content. Editing a URL replaces the managed line; clearing a URL removes only the managed line, and URL add/replace/clear preserve non-managed note text exactly, including whitespace, blank lines, empty strings, and newline style.\n\nValidated with `make check`. Live EventKit proof on macOS 27.0 (26A5368g) with Reminders full access: adding a reminder with `--url https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-managed-proof` returned notes containing `remindctl URL (managed): https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-managed-proof`, editing to `https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-managed-proof-v2` replaced that managed line, and `--clear-url` removed the URL field while leaving the authored notes as `Codex proof notes`; the disposable proof reminder was deleted afterward. Added regression coverage for authored `URL: ...` lines, authored plain `remindctl URL: ...` lines, notes-only text, URL replace/clear with authored whitespace and newline style, and empty-string notes on URL clear.\n",
        "branch": "fix-reminder-url-field",
